Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @Sweet Potato{1} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30} and @Red Leicester{30}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150} and season again, then stir-fry until browned, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Do this in batches if your pan is small - you want the mushrooms to fry, not stew.

Once the veg is cooked, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Meanwhile, put the @Red Wine Vinegar{12} and @Olive Oil{1} for the dressing into a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together. Set the dressing aside. In another small #bowl{}, combine the @Tomato Puree{30} and @Water{1} for the sauce.

Arrange your @Plain Taco Tortillas{4} (2 per person) on a #baking tray{} and cover with the tomato puree mix, leaving a 1cm border around the edge. Share the mushrooms and peppers between the tortillas, then top with the grated @Double Gloucester{30} and other cheeses. Bake the tortizzas in the oven until golden and the cheese is bubbly, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Add the @Wild Rocket{40} to the bowl of dressing and toss together. When the tortizzas are ready, transfer them to your plates and serve with the sweet potato chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!